  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You know how to strike subtly and exploit a foe's distraction. Once per turn, you can deal an extra [[/r 1d6]] damage to one creature you hit with a weapon attack if you have advantage on the attack roll. This damage is the same as the weapon's damage, and the attack must use a finesse or a ranged weapon.</p>\n<p>You don't need advantage on the attack roll if another enemy of the target is within 5 feet of it, that enemy isn't incapacitated, and you don't have disadvantage on the attack roll.</p>\n<p>You can deal this additional damage a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus. You regain all expended uses when you complete a long rest.</p>",
